> Don,t know if this is the correct way to go about
> it, but I am using the
> following method with Wsety Jalousie windws with
> very good results. I am
> using steel wool. I reorted to it because the finish
> was soooooo bad.
> They are coming out real nice. When I paint the bus,
> I will pull them
> again and polish em up probably with semichrome
> polish (in all good
> motorcycle shops) and spray them with a coat of
> clear from a spray bomb
> to prevent them from tarnishing.
> 
> The screws holding in the windows had rusted and
> were staining the
> window. Went to the hardware staor and got a box of
> stainless for $3.43
> that is enough to do all the windows. I was
> wondering if the original
> screws were stainless and just rusted after fourty
> years of exposure. Or
> was westfalia just too cheap to spend a couple bucks
